The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Silvio trial 

 Milan, July 7 (Reuters): An Italian judge today ordered former Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi to stand trial over alleged fraud at broadcaster Mediaset. 

 The case follows a four-year probe into claims of embezzlement, false accounting, tax fraud and money laundering in television rights deals between 1994 and 1999. 

 Spain flu 

 Madrid (Reuters) - A Spanish laboratory has confirmed the countrys first case of H5N1 bird flu after analysing a sample taken from a migratory water bird. 

 Korea threat 

 Seoul (Reuters): North Korea threatened Japan on Friday for imposing sanctions after it test-fired missiles on Wednesday. 

 Pavarotti 

 London (Reuters): Luciano Pavarotti, 70, regarded by many as the greatest operatic tenor of his generation, has undergone surgery for pancreatic cancer and is in a US hospital recovering, his manager said. 




